Vision
Create an automated, reproducible research pipeline that transforms live sports data into public-facing statistical analysis published on mr.danoff.org.

The system will demonstrate:

API integration

Data engineering & pace-neutral feature extraction

Bayesian hierarchical modeling (MCMC)

Reproducible research

Peeragogy principles

Automated web publishing

The initial use case will be the 2026 NBA Finals between the San Antonio Spurs and New York Knicks.

Problem Statement
Current workflow requires:

Manual SportRadar API queries and endpoint verification

Manual game ID discovery

Manual CSV generation and data-type casting

Manual Bayesian model execution

Manual HTML updates

Manual publishing

This creates unnecessary effort, limits scalability, and increases the chance of human error.

