Functional Requirements
FR-1 Data Collection
System shall:

Connect to SportRadar API v8 summary endpoints.

Auto-discover relevant game IDs from schedule payloads.

Handle API 429 rate limits via exponential backoff.

Store raw responses for auditing.

Output: raw_summary.json

FR-2 Data Processing & Feature Engineering
System shall:

Parse deep game summaries and player arrays.

Execute mathematical fallbacks for missing aggregate data (e.g., manually summing player turnovers).

Calculate pace-neutral metrics (Effective FG%, Turnover %, Offensive Rebound %, FT Rate).

Export a standardized, type-safe CSV.

Output: spurs_2026_all24_four_factors.csv

FR-3 Bayesian Analysis
System shall:

Execute a 3-hierarchy Bayesian Logistic Regression model (Finals, Pre-Finals, Other Playoffs).

Utilize a custom Adaptive Metropolis-Hastings sampler to generate 10,000 posterior draws.

Calculate exact game-to-series combinatorics (e.g., P(win 3 before losing 2)).

Extract posterior medians and 90% Credible Intervals (CI).

Output: posterior_results.json

FR-4 HTML Generation
System shall:

Generate article pages using the daLab Fiesta-glass visual system.

Update Chart.js log-normal density plots dynamically.

Insert latest MCMC posterior summaries.

Preserve historical versions.

Outputs:
game3-analysis.html
game4-analysis.html
final-retrospective.html

FR-5 Automated Publishing
System shall:

Deploy generated pages.

Publish to mr.danoff.org.

Maintain version history.

